    "subheading": "Airbnb, VRBO, and Booking.com don&rsquo;t pay you the nightly rate &mdash; they pay a net deposit after service fees, cleaning, taxes withheld, and timing splits. TechBrot&rsquo;s Certified QuickBooks ProAdvisors reconcile every platform payout to gross, build a real profit and loss for each listing, and record lodging and occupancy tax correctly &mdash; so your per-property numbers are true and your books are ready for your CPA. Independent firm, not affiliated with Intuit Inc., Airbnb, or VRBO.",
    "actions": [
      { "label": "Book the discovery call", "href": "/contact/?intent=accounting", "class": "btn--primary" },
      { "label": "Get the free file review", "href": "/quickbooks/file-review/?intent=file-review", "class": "btn--ghost" },
      { "label": "Speak to a ProAdvisor", "tel": true, "class": "btn--ghost" }
    ]
  },
  "inBrief": {
    "text": "Short-term rental books break where ordinary bookkeeping never has to look: the <strong>net deposit a platform pays you is not your revenue</strong>. Airbnb, VRBO, and Booking.com each net out service fees, cleaning, and sometimes taxes before the money lands, so the books have to be reconciled <strong>gross-to-net per payout and per listing</strong> &mdash; or your income is understated, your fees are invisible, and you can&rsquo;t tell which property actually earns. <strong>TechBrot</strong> is a firm of <a href=\"/quickbooks/proadvisor-team/\">Certified QuickBooks ProAdvisors</a> who reconcile every platform payout to gross, build a <a href=\"/accounting/bookkeeping/\">per-listing profit and loss</a>, track cleaning and turnover cost, record lodging and occupancy tax correctly, and connect your channel manager or PMS to your own QuickBooks file. We keep the books; your CPA decides the tax classification and files. For multi-property hosts ready to act on the numbers, <a href=\"/accounting/advisory/fractional-cfo/\">advisory</a> adds the judgment layer on top.",
    "source": "Maintained by the Certified QuickBooks ProAdvisor team at TechBrot Inc., an independent firm &mdash; not affiliated with Intuit Inc., Airbnb, Inc., or any booking platform. TechBrot keeps the books; your CPA or EA files income taxes and decides Schedule C vs. Schedule E classification and depreciation treatment."
  },
  "ctaBand": {
    "eyebrow": "Ready when you are",
    "heading": "Get short-term rental books that tie to the deposit.",
    "lede": "Book a 30-minute discovery call. We&rsquo;ll review your listings, your platforms, where the payouts stop reconciling, and the right next step &mdash; with a written fixed-fee scope within 3 business days. No pitch. Independent firm &mdash; does not file income taxes; coordinates with your CPA or EA.",
